# Development Workflow

## Quality gate — before "done"

```bash
flutter pub get
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs  # routes / DI / drift / annotations
flutter analyze                                            # must be "No issues found!"
```

Commands use plain `flutter` (no pinned `.fvmrc`). If you use FVM, prefix with
`fvm` — same toolchain (Flutter 3.44).

## Code generation

Run `build_runner` after changing any of:

- `@RoutePage()` routes (`auto_route` → `app_router.gr.dart`)
- `@injectable` / `@lazySingleton` DI (`injectable` → `di_container.config.dart`)
- drift tables/queries (`drift_dev` → `app_database.g.dart`)

Never hand-edit generated `*.g.dart` / `*.gr.dart` / `*.config.dart`.

## Dependency Injection

```dart
@injectable            // new instance each resolve
@lazySingleton         // lazy singleton
@Injectable(as: Repo)  // register behind an interface

final bloc = getIt<LibraryBloc>();  // at page/Bloc creation, never inside build()
```

## Routing

`@RoutePage()` on pages; route tree in `lib/core/routing/app_router.dart`.
Navigate with `context.router` / `context.pushRoute(...)`.

## Persistence

- **drift** database in `lib/core/database/app_database.dart`; repositories expose
  `Stream`s the Blocs subscribe to. Map rows → domain entities at the data edge.
- **Preferences**: one typed store per concern over `shared_preferences`
  (`LibraryPreferences`, `ReaderPreferences`, …); reactive ones expose a
  `ValueNotifier`.

## Localization

Add keys to `assets/translations/en.json` (nested by feature). No generation step
— used at runtime via `.tr()`. Add a `<locale>.json` with the same shape for a
new language.
